<p>Italian is the language of art, music, and cuisine, spoken by over 85 million people worldwide. Italy has the third largest economy in the Eurozone, and Italian is an official language of the European Union. Italian pronunciation is highly phonetic, meaning words are pronounced as they are written. This makes Italian easier to read aloud correctly compared to languages like English or French. FluentCards TTS feature provides accurate Italian pronunciation for every card, helping you develop authentic pronunciation.</p><p>Italian vocabulary shares many cognates with English due to common Latin origins. Words ending in -tion in English often correspond to -zione in Italian, -sion becomes -sione, and -ty becomes -ta. Recognizing these patterns can dramatically accelerate vocabulary acquisition. The Italian Basics deck includes 30 essential words covering greetings, verbs, numbers, and everyday vocabulary. Consistent daily practice with the FSRS algorithm ensures you retain what you learn and build a strong foundation for conversation.</p>
<p>Italian vocabulary acquisition can be accelerated by recognizing patterns between Italian and English. Thousands of Italian words are cognates or near-cognates with English due to their shared Latin heritage. For example, Italian words ending in -zione correspond to English -tion, -sione corresponds to -sion, and -mente corresponds to -ly adverbs. Creating flashcards that explicitly highlight these patterns helps your brain form connections between existing English knowledge and new Italian vocabulary. The Italian Basics deck provides a foundation of 30 essential words, and the FSRS algorithm ensures efficient scheduling of reviews for optimal long-term retention.</p>
